cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the Impact Factor normalization in terms of differences in citation potentials among fields of science, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely because they deal with citation analysis and bibliometrics. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also possible because they involve interdisciplinary research and the impact of research in different fields. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely but still possible category because it deals with the statistical testing of differences in distributions.
